{
  "texts": [
    "The MAPF problem consists of a set of agents, obstacles, and target points in a given map.",
    "The main objective is to compute collision-free paths where all agents can reach assigned targets from their start locations.",
    "Once multiple feasible paths are found, the problem can then be regarded as an optimization problem since the aim is to identify the paths that optimize a given objective function.",
    "From a classical point of view (Stern 2019), MAPF with N agents, M dynamic, and K static obstacles can be defined as a tuple:",
    "a set of static obstacles."
  ]
}